Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 20:05:01 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?patch:=20drop=20chatbot/AnsibleAIConnect=20watc?=
 =?UTF-8?q?h=20=E2=80=94=20MCP-only=20build?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The upstream watches.yaml lists BOTH AnsibleAIConnect (chatbot/Lightspeed)
and AnsibleMCPConnect (MCP). For our MCP-only deployment the chart's
manager-rbac is narrowed to mcpconnect.ansible.com, AND we deliberately
skip snapshotting the aiconnect.ansible.com CRD.

Result without this patch: operator startup hits

    error: 'failed to get restmapping: no matches for kind "AnsibleAIConnect"
    in group "aiconnect.ansible.com"'

— controller-runtime tries to set up a watch on a CRD that doesn't exist
in the cluster. Not fatal (it retries forever) but noisy and may slow MCP
reconcile.

Drop the AnsibleAIConnect watch entry. Image becomes genuinely MCP-only
at the static-config level. The roles/chatbot/ + playbooks/ansibleaiconnect.yml
files still ship in the image — harmless dead code we leave alone for
upstream-pure parity.
---
 watches.yaml | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/watches.yaml b/watches.yaml
index 7ed9839..f76fc67 100644
--- a/watches.yaml
+++ b/watches.yaml
@@ -1,9 +1,5 @@
 ---
 # Use the 'create api' subcommand to add watches to this file.
-- version: v1alpha1
-  group: aiconnect.ansible.com
-  kind: AnsibleAIConnect
-  playbook: playbooks/ansibleaiconnect.yml
 - version: v1alpha1
   group: mcpconnect.ansible.com
   kind: AnsibleMCPConnect
